title: About Steve
text:
Unleashing the Power of Data for Healthcare Accessibility
As a biochemistry enthusiast, Steve’s insatiable curiosity led him to explore the world of data analysis. He pursued a comprehensive education in Biochemistry, equipping him with a profound understanding of the subject. It was during this journey that he discovered his true passion for unraveling patterns and insights from complex data sets.



Steven


Currently, Steven serves as a key contributor at 39 North Labs, forefronting the companies first healthcare accessibility analysis.

Unleashing the Power of Data for Healthcare Accessibility 
 



 
Steve, a biochemistry major ventured into the realm of data analysis. His comprehensive education in Biochemistry equipped him with a deep understanding of the subject which enabled him to unearth his genuine love for deciphering patterns and insights from intricate data sets.
Apart from his data-driven pursuits, Steve finds joy in outdoor activities like hiking and swimming. As well as being an avid drummer from the age of 13, so you may catch him on the weekends playing a show at your favorite bar!
Currently, Steve plays a pivotal role as a contributor at 39 North Labs, where he spearheads innovative approaches in spacial health analytics, striving to revolutionize the evaluation and improvement of healthcare accessibility.
